        "title": "2. `scrollTimelines.ts` â€” `buildCameraTimeline` untested",
        "content": "\n**Gaps:**\n- No test that `gsap.set` initial values are applied (`landscape` scale 1, `haze` alpha 0, `train` alpha 1/scale 1) â€” a regression here would silently break the opening frame.\n- No test that the returned timeline actually contains a `ScrollTrigger` bound to `spacer` with `scrub: 1.2` â€” this is the entire mechanism tying scroll to animation, and it's config, not logic, so it only breaks silently.\n- No verification of keyframe **ordering/timing** invariants (haze fades in before it fades out; train blur starts before its full opacity fade; foreground scale reaches 6 by duration 0.9) â€” a copy-paste edit to a `duration` or position argument wouldn't be caught by anything.\n- Missing-ref / null-element handling: the function destructures `refs` and calls `gsap.set` directly â€” no test for what happens if `spacer`/`landscape`/etc. is `null` (TS would allow this to compile since `CameraRefs` isn't marked optional, but nothing guards runtime misuse from a caller that doesn't type-check, e.g. a ref not yet attached during effect timing).\n- Return value contract: callers presumably call `.kill()` on this timeline for cleanup â€” no test asserts the timeline is a real killable GSAP timeline (vs., say, a plain object) and that ScrollTrigger instances get killed with it (a very common GSAP memory-leak source in SPAs).\n\n```ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, vi } from 'vitest'\nimport gsap from 'gsap'\nimport { ScrollTrigger } from 'gsap/ScrollTrigger'\nimport { buildCameraTimeline } from './scrollTimelines'\n\ngsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger)\n\nfunction makeRefs() {\n  return {\n    spacer: document.createElement('div'),\n    landscape: document.createElement('div'),\n    haze: document.createElement('div'),\n    train: document.createElement('div'),\n  }\n}\n\ndescribe('buildCameraTimeline', () => {\n  beforeEach(() => {\n    document.body.innerHTML = ''\n  })\n\n  it('sets initial transform state on all three layers', () => {\n    const refs = makeRefs()\n    document.body.append(refs.spacer, refs.landscape, refs.haze, refs.train)\n    buildCameraTimeline(refs)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.landscape, 'scale')).toBe(1)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.haze, 'autoAlpha')).toBe(0)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.train, 'autoAlpha')).toBe(1)\n  })\n\n  it('binds a ScrollTrigger to the spacer with scrub enabled', () => {\n    const refs = makeRefs()\n    document.body.append(refs.spacer, refs.landscape, refs.haze, refs.train)\n    const tl = buildCameraTimeline(refs)\n    const st = tl.scrollTrigger\n    expect(st).toBeTruthy()\n    expect(st!.vars.trigger).toBe(refs.spacer)\n    expect(st!.vars.scrub).toBe(1.2)\n  })\n\n  it('returns a killable timeline whose ScrollTrigger is also killed on tl.kill()', () => {\n    const refs = makeRefs()\n    document.body.append(refs.spacer, refs.landscape, refs.haze, refs.train)\n    const tl = buildCameraTimeline(refs)\n    const st = tl.scrollTrigger!\n    const killSpy = vi.spyOn(st, 'kill')\n    tl.kill()\n    expect(killSpy).toHaveBeenCalled()\n  })\n\n  it('train reaches scale 6 and fully fades out by the end of the timeline', () => {\n    const refs = makeRefs()\n    document.body.append(refs.spacer, refs.landscape, refs.haze, refs.train)\n    const tl = buildCameraTimeline(refs)\n    tl.progress(1)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.train, 'scale')).toBeCloseTo(6, 1)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.train, 'autoAlpha')).toBeCloseTo(0, 1)\n  })\n\n  it('haze peaks mid-timeline then clears by the end', () => {\n    const refs = makeRefs()\n    document.body.append(refs.spacer, refs.landscape, refs.haze, refs.train)\n    const tl = buildCameraTimeline(refs)\n    tl.progress(0.6)\n    const mid = gsap.getProperty(refs.haze, 'autoAlpha') as number\n    tl.progress(1)\n    expect(mid).toBeGreaterThan(0)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.haze, 'autoAlpha')).toBeCloseTo(0, 1)\n  })\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "3. `useLenis.ts` â€” untested hook, biggest integration gap",
        "content": "\n**Gaps:**\n- No test that mounting the hook creates a `Lenis` instance and registers it via `lenisStore.set`.\n- **Cleanup is the highest-risk untested path**: unmount must call `gsap.ticker.remove(raf)`, `lenis.destroy()`, and `lenisStore.set(null)`. Missing any one of these is a memory leak / zombie scroll listener that only shows up after repeated mount/unmount (e.g., route changes, HMR) â€” exactly the kind of bug unit tests catch and manual QA doesn't.\n- No test that `lenis.on('scroll', ScrollTrigger.update)` is actually wired (i.e., a scroll event drives `ScrollTrigger.update`) â€” without this, every scrubbed timeline in the app silently stops updating.\n- No test for double-mount (React 18 StrictMode double-invokes effects in dev) â€” does `useLenis` end up with two Lenis instances / two ticker callbacks?\n\n```ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, vi, afterEach } from 'vitest'\nimport { renderHook } from '@testing-library/react'\nimport gsap from 'gsap'\nimport { ScrollTrigger } from 'gsap/ScrollTrigger'\nimport Lenis from 'lenis'\nimport { useLenis } from './useLenis'\nimport { lenisStore } from './lenisStore'\n\nvi.mock('lenis')\nvi.mock('./lenisStore', () => ({ lenisStore: { set: vi.fn() } }))\n\ndescribe('useLenis', () => {\n  afterEach(() => vi.clearAllMocks())\n\n  it('creates a Lenis instance and registers it in lenisStore on mount', () => {\n    renderHook(() => useLenis())\n    expect(Lenis).toHaveBeenCalledOnce()\n    expect(lenisStore.set).toHaveBeenCalledWith(expect.any(Object))\n  })\n\n  it('wires lenis scroll events to ScrollTrigger.update', () => {\n    const onSpy = vi.fn()\n    ;(Lenis as any).mockImplementation(() => ({ on: onSpy, raf: vi.fn(), destroy: vi.fn() }))\n    renderHook(() => useLenis())\n    expect(onSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith('scroll', ScrollTrigger.update)\n  })\n\n  it('destroys lenis, removes the ticker callback, and clears the store on unmount', () => {\n    const destroy = vi.fn()\n    const removeSpy = vi.spyOn(gsap.ticker, 'remove')\n    ;(Lenis as any).mockImplementation(() => ({ on: vi.fn(), raf: vi.fn(), destroy }))\n    const { unmount } = renderHook(() => useLenis())\n    unmount()\n    expect(destroy).toHaveBeenCalledOnce()\n    expect(removeSpy).toHaveBeenCalled()\n    expect(lenisStore.set).toHaveBeenLastCalledWith(null)\n  })\n\n  it('does not leak a second ticker callback across StrictMode double-invoke', () => {\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(gsap.ticker, 'add')\n    const { unmount, rerender } = renderHook(() => useLenis())\n    unmount()\n    rerender()\n    // second mount after cleanup should register exactly one new raf, not stack up\n    expect(addSpy).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(2) // 1 per real mount, not per StrictMode phantom\n  })\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "4. `useMouseParallax.ts` â€” largest number of untested branches",
        "content": "\n**Gaps (all currently 0% covered):**\n- **Early-return guards** â€” the two most important branches in the file:\n  - `landscapeRef.current` or `trainRef.current` is `null` â†’ must return without attaching listeners.\n  - `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` â†’ must skip entirely (accessibility requirement, explicitly called out in the code comment).\n  - `pointer: fine` false (touch devices) â†’ must skip entirely.\n- No test that a `pointermove` event actually updates `x`/`y`/`rotationX`/`rotationY` on the two elements via `gsap.quickTo`.\n- No test for **clamping**: cursor coordinates outside the viewport (or a resize making `clientX > innerWidth`) should still clamp `nx`/`ny` to `[-1, 1]` rather than producing a runaway transform.\n- No test for the **sign/direction contract**: background and foreground move *opposite* the cursor (`-nx`, `-ny`) while rotation moves *toward* it (`+nx`/`-ny` per axis) â€” this is exactly the kind of \"reads correct in review, silently flips in a refactor\" bug that a snapshot-style assertion catches immediately.\n- No test that cleanup (unmount / effect re-run) removes the `pointermove` listener â€” currently truncated file cuts off before showing the return/cleanup, so it's unverified whether a listener leak exists at all.\n- No test verifying the two independent transform channels (mouse: x/y/rotationX/rotationY vs. scroll: scale/yPercent, per the docstring) don't clobber each other when both fire in the same frame â€” this is called out as \"the whole game\" in the comment but has zero regression protection.\n\n```ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, vi, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest'\nimport { renderHook } from '@testing-library/react'\nimport gsap from 'gsap'\nimport { useMouseParallax } from './useMouseParallax'\n\nfunction mockMatchMedia(overrides: Record<string, boolean>) {\n  vi.stubGlobal('matchMedia', (query: string) => ({\n    matches: Object.entries(overrides).some(([k, v]) => query.includes(k) && v),\n    addEventListener: vi.fn(),\n    removeEventListener: vi.fn(),\n  }))\n}\n\ndescribe('useMouseParallax', () => {\n  let landscape: HTMLDivElement, train: HTMLDivElement\n  beforeEach(() => {\n    landscape = document.createElement('div')\n    train = document.createElement('div')\n    document.body.append(landscape, train)\n  })\n  afterEach(() => {\n    document.body.innerHTML = ''\n    vi.unstubAllGlobals()\n  })\n\n  it('skips attaching listeners when reduced motion is preferred', () => {\n    mockMatchMedia({ 'prefers-reduced-motion': true, 'pointer: fine': true })\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'addEventListener')\n    renderHook(() =>\n      useMouseParallax({ current: landscape } as any, { current: train } as any),\n    )\n    expect(addSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.anything())\n  })\n\n  it('skips attaching listeners on coarse/touch pointers', () => {\n    mockMatchMedia({ 'prefers-reduced-motion': false, 'pointer: fine': false })\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'addEventListener')\n    renderHook(() =>\n      useMouseParallax({ current: landscape } as any, { current: train } as any),\n    )\n    expect(addSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.anything())\n  })\n\n  it('no-ops when either ref is null', () => {\n    mockMatchMedia({ 'prefers-reduced-motion': false, 'pointer: fine': true })\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'addEventListener')\n    renderHook(() =>\n      useMouseParallax({ current: null } as any, { current: train } as any),\n    )\n    expect(addSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.anything())\n  })\n\n  it('moves background opposite and foreground opposite-but-larger than the cursor', () => {\n    mockMatchMedia({ 'prefers-reduced-motion': false, 'pointer: fine': true })\n    renderHook(() =>\n      useMouseParallax({ current: landscape } as any, { current: train } as any),\n    )\n    window.dispatchEvent(new PointerEvent('pointermove', { clientX: window.innerWidth, clientY: window.innerHeight / 2 }))\n    gsap.ticker.tick() // flush quickTo\n    const bgX = gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'x') as number\n    const fgX = gsap.getProperty(train, 'x') as number\n    expect(bgX).toBeLessThan(0)          // cursor at right edge -> layers shift left\n    expect(Math.abs(fgX)).toBeGreaterThan(Math.abs(bgX)) // foreground travels further\n  })\n\n  it('clamps cursor offset outside the viewport instead of extrapolating', () => {\n    mockMatchMedia({ 'prefers-reduced-motion': false, 'pointer: fine': true })\n    renderHook(() =>\n      useMouseParallax({ current: landscape } as any, { current: train } as any),\n    )\n    window.dispatchEvent(new PointerEvent('pointermove', { clientX: window.innerWidth * 3, clientY: 0 }))\n    gsap.ticker.tick()\n    // at clamp nx=1 the max displacement is exactly BG_SHIFT_X; must not exceed it\n    expect(Math.abs(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'x') as number)).toBeLessThanOrEqual(10)\n  })\n\n  it('removes the pointermove listener on unmount', () => {\n    mockMatchMedia({ 'prefers-reduced-motion': false, 'pointer: fine': true })\n    const removeSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'removeEventListener')\n    const { unmount } = renderHook(() =>\n      useMouseParallax({ current: landscape } as any, { current: train } as any),\n    )\n    unmount()\n    expect(removeSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function))\n  })\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "5. `contactRevealEvent.ts` â€” trivial, no test needed",
        "content": "It's a single exported string constant. ponytail: a test here would just re-assert the literal â€” skip, add only if the event name ever needs cross-file synchronization logic (e.g., a namespacing scheme).\n\n**But this exposes a real integration gap**: `CONTACT_REVEALED` is a bare string used as a custom-event name across `WorkSection` (dispatcher) and `ContactModal`/contact section (listener). Nothing tests that:\n- `WorkSection`'s pin ScrollTrigger actually dispatches `window.dispatchEvent(new Event(CONTACT_REVEALED))` exactly once when phase-2 slide-off completes.\n- The contact section's listener fires exactly once and doesn't re-hide afterward (the comment explicitly says \"never hides again\" â€” that's a stateful invariant with zero regression coverage).\n- Rapid scroll-up-then-down doesn't fire the event twice or fire it before the animation actually completes.\n\n```ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, vi } from 'vitest'\nimport { CONTACT_REVEALED } from './contactRevealEvent'\n\ndescribe('CONTACT_REVEALED integration (WorkSection -> ContactSection)', () => {\n  it('dispatches CONTACT_REVEALED exactly once when phase-2 slide-off completes', () => {\n    const handler = vi.fn()\n    window.addEventListener(CONTACT_REVEALED, handler)\n    // TODO: mount WorkSection, drive its ScrollTrigger to end of phase 2\n    // (requires a WorkSection-specific test harness â€” flagging as the gap)\n    window.removeEventListener(CONTACT_REVEALED, handler)\n  })\n\n  it('contact section stays revealed after the event fires even if scrolled back up', () => {\n    // TODO: mount contact section, dispatch CONTACT_REVEALED, scroll position back\n    // to 0, assert visibility state is still \"revealed\"\n  })\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "Summary table",
        "content": "| File | Untested units | Highest-risk gap |\n|---|---|---|\n| `lenisStore.ts` | 4 methods | calls before `set()` â€” relies on untested optional chaining |\n| `scrollTimelines.ts` | 1 function, 3 layers, keyframe timing | ScrollTrigger/timeline leak on `.kill()` |\n| `useLenis.ts` | mount/unmount lifecycle | cleanup leak (ticker/instance/store not cleared) on unmount |\n| `useMouseParallax.ts` | 2 guard branches, direction/clamp math, cleanup | reduced-motion / touch guards â€” accessibility regression risk |\n| `contactRevealEvent.ts` | n/a (trivial) | cross-component event contract (fire-once, no re-hide) untested |\n\nBiggest single recommendation: **install Vitest + Testing Library** (nothing else is possible until then), then prioritize `useLenis` cleanup and `useMouseParallax` accessibility guards â€” both are silent-failure modes (leaks, missed a11y preference) that won't show up in manual testing.",
        "level": 2
      }
    ],
